<anchor id="sema_8h_1sema"/> <simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>A semaphore is simply a variable that is non-negative and is shared between threads. It is a signaling mechanism for low-level synchronization of threads and/or tasks. It uses the two atomic operations Wait and Signal for the process synchronization. <linebreak/>
 Counting semaphores uses a count that helps tasks to be acquired or released numerous times. If the count is 0, the counting semaphore is in the unavailable state, If the count is greater 0, the semaphore is in the available state and the number of tokens it has is equal to its count.</para>
</simplesect>
